class Solution {
public:
    string removeOuterParentheses(string S) {
        stack<char> open;
        queue<char> primitive;
        string output;
        for(int i=0; i<S.length(); i++) {
            primitive.push(S[i]);
            if(S[i] == '(') {
                open.push(S[i]);
            }
            else {
                open.pop();
                if(open.empty()) {
                    primitive.pop();
                    while(!primitive.empty()) {
                        output.push_back(primitive.front());
                        primitive.pop();
                    }
                    output.pop_back();
                }
            }
        }
        return output;
    }
};
```

Stack stores the opening brackets. Once the stack is empty, we found one primitive. Primitives are stored in queue. We remove the outer brackets and store in output.

