The question seems to be difficult but its rather easy to understand.
The main idea here is to understand that the given string is already a valid parenthesis and the main requirement is to just remove the outermost bracket of the simplest valid parenthesis that can be done using the **counting method** what it means is that the number of opening brackets is same as closing bracket for a given sub valid parenthesis string.
Take two pointer i and j both at zero and start counting the opening brackets and reducing the count on closing bracket once the count reaches zero that means we have a valid parenthesis and we can now remove the given set of brackets and then update i to j+1 to the next opening bracket if it exits and then also incrementing j so that the above initial step can be repeated.

