# Intuition
As you know, we should give back nums array with same length so I decided to overrite array elements with updated one.

# Approach
The algorithm iterates through the input array using a single loop, and uses a variable 'sum' to keep track of the running sum. At each iteration, the current element of the array is assigned the current value of the running sum, and the 'sum' variable is updated to include the next element in the array.

Finally, the modified input array containing the running sums is returned.

Overall, this is a simple and efficient approach to calculate running sums, and it does not require any additional data structures or complex computations.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n)

- Space complexity:
O(1)

# Code
```
/**
 * @param {number[]} nums
 * @return {number[]}
 */
var runningSum = function(nums) {
    //TIME-COMPLEXITY: O(n);
    //MEMORY: O(1);
    let sum = nums[0];
    for(let i = 0; i < nums.length; i++){
        nums[i] = sum;
        if(i+1 < nums.length){
            sum += nums[i+1]
        }
    }
    return nums;
};
```

