```
Explanation : (Prefix Sum) 

	 Here I'm taking first example TestCase of leetcode

	 nums = [1, 2, 3, 4]

	 Inner Working of Prefix Sum Approach

	 steps :
	 1. create prefixSum array with nums array length --> {0, 0, 0,0};
	 2. add 0th index element of nums array to prefixSum array, prefixSum[0] = nums[0];

	 for (int i = 1; i < nums.length; i++) {
		 prefixSum[i] = prefixSum[i - 1] + nums[i];
	 }

	 how this loop is working ?

	 intial prefixSum array = {1, 0, 0, 0}

	 consider,
	 i = 1;
	 prefixSum[i] = prefixSum[i - 1] + nums[i], it means,
	 prefixSum[1] = prefixSum[1 - 1] + nums[1],
	 prefixSum[1] = prefixSum[0] + nums[1] // calculate answers;
	 prefixSum[1] = 1 + 2;
	 prefixSum[1] = 3;
	 prefixSum array = {1, 3, 0, 0}

	 similarly, for i = 2;
	 prefixSum[i] = prefixSum[i - 1] + nums[i], it means,
	 prefixSum[2] = prefixSum[2 - 1] + nums[2],
	 prefixSum[2] = prefixSum[1] + nums[2] // calculate answers;
	 prefixSum[2] = 3 + 3;
	 prefixSum[2] = 6;
	 prefixSum array = {1, 3, 6, 0}

